sec.p:
For photoconductive detectors, the photoresponsivity depends on: 1) the intrinsic properties of photosensitive materials, such as carrier collection efficiency μτ (τ is the carrier lifetime, μ is the carrier mobility); 2) device structure, such as the spacing between positive and negative electrodes. Photoconductive gain (G) can be used as a bridge to deduce the specific expression. The current responsivity Rλ can be defined as Rλ = Iph/Pin (Iph is the photocurrent, Pin is the input optical power), which can be specifically expressed by the following formula [27].
Rλ=μτVηeλL2hc=EQEeλhc\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
